Date:  26/10/1894
Source:  Wanganui Herald
Author:
Vol / Page:  2
Edition:
Quote:  There had been a raffle for a horse, and as the winner was going out to lead him away the landlord of the bush hotel, always keen for business, said, "Shure'n you'll shout for all hands after that lump o' luck; you're not the wan to take a shingle off a poor man's roof, I'll be bound."
